===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|India|lang=la}} from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|Ἰνδία|tr=India|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|Ἰνδός||Indus River|tr=Indos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{etyl|peo}} hinduš {{rfscript|Old Persian Cuneiform}} (Persian {{term|هند|lang=fa|tr=Hend|sc=fa-Arab}}) from {{etyl|sa}}  {{term|सिन्धु||a river, stream|tr=síndhu|lang=sa|sc=Deva}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|ĭnʹdēə}}, {{IPA|/ˈɪndiə/}}, {{SAMPA|/"Indi@/}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# The territory east of the river [[Indus]] and south of the [[Himalaya]] mountains (formerly also known as [[Hindustan]])
# Country in South Asia ([[Bharat]]). Official name: Republic of India.
# Formerly applied to [[America]], also pl. [[Indies]] (obsolete)
# The letter ''[[I]]'' in the [[ICAO spelling alphabet]].

